  "observations": [
    "Daily Note as primary entry point — opening Roam lands on today's yyyy-mm-dd page, no separate dashboard",
    "Every block has a stable UUID — granularity of reference is block, not page (((uuid)) syntax)",
    "Pages are pure outlines — no rich page-level metadata; structure expressed entirely as nested bullets",
    "Block embeds are live mirrors — editing source updates all embed sites, distinguishing embed from copy",
    "Footer of every page splits into two sections: Linked References (explicit [[]]) and Unlinked Mentions (string-match)",
    "Unlinked mentions offer one-click promotion to Linked references, materializing latent backlinks",
    "Zoom-into-block replaces workspace with the subtree, breadcrumb shows ancestor path back to page",
    "Right sidebar acts as stacked workspace — multiple pages/blocks open in parallel via shift-click",
    "Queries live inside blocks ({{[[query]]: ...}}) — DSL with AND/OR/NOT/BETWEEN, evaluated on render",
    "TODO is a query-aggregable marker, not a status field — checkbox sentinel inside block content",
    "Attributes (Key:: Value) are KV-rows embedded in prose, queryable across the graph as a virtual table",
    "Tags (#x) are syntactic alias for [[x]] — same backlink semantics, different surface",
    "Cmd-U quick-open and Cmd-Shift-9 full-text-with-filters are the two primary navigation modalities",
    "Permissions are graph-level binary (Editor/Reader); public graphs expose read-only via custom URL",
    "Plugin code (roam/css, roam/js) lives as content of special pages — self-modifying graph as extension surface",
    "Multi-select across blocks enables group operations (move, copy reference, recolor) as bulk action",
    "Deep undo history covers structural edits — indent/outdent/move are reversible without explicit checkpoints"
  ]
